    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the input shaft into main drive gear splines (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l0">Figure 210</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l0" filename="../figg13/G13017L0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 210. Input Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the input shaft just far enough into the gear to expose the drive gear I.D. snap
                ring groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear I.D. snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l1">Figure 211</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l1" filename="../figg13/G13017L1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 211. Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear spacer on the input shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l2">Figure 212</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l2" filename="../figg13/G13017L2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 212. Drive Gear Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the external snap ring to the outside, slide the drive gear bearing on the input shaft
                and position into the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l2">Figure 212</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the input shaft bearing driver, seat the bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l3">Figure 213</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l3" filename="../figg13/G13017L3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 213. Seat The Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing retainer snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l4">Figure 214</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017l4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017l4" filename="../figg13/G13017L4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 214. Align Oil Return Holes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on the transmission mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l4">Figure 214</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the front bearing cover on the input shaft. Align the oil return hole in the cover
                with the oil return hole on the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017l4">Figure 214</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
